bcl:definition.bcl:text:
revenue sharing taxes means Class 4 property value taxes imposed by
one municipality, a portion of which is paid over to another municipality as tax sharing
revenue;

bcl:paragraph.bcl:text:
subject to section 5 [cap on Class 4 property
              revenue] of this regulation, tax sharing revenue received from another
            municipality as provided for by letters patent;

revenue received under an agreement, other than gifts or grants received under
            an agreement or amounts included as revenue under another paragraph of this
            section;

revenue received under section 5 [compensation to local
              governments] of the Ports Property Tax
                Act;

in any other case, the average municipal tax rate on Class 4 property in
                British Columbia for the year, as determined by the inspector of
                municipalities;
